        repairandprocess: 'Single Door refrigerator servicing starts with a temperature measurement of the main compartment and freezer section to establish a baseline. The technician then inspects the condenser coils at the back of the fridge for dust buildup and cleans them if required — dirty condenser coils are a major cause of high electricity consumption and poor cooling. The door gasket is inspected for any tears or gaps that allow warm air to enter. The thermostat setting is verified and calibrated if needed. The compressor is checked for current draw and unusual noise. Refrigerant pressure is assessed. A final temperature check is done after 30 minutes to verify cooling improvement.',
